From 57cf7956f6b6aec993476b8e8c987496c9e2abf9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Rouven Czerwinski <r.czerwinski@pengutronix.de>
Date: Fri, 19 Nov 2021 17:32:48 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 16/25] epc660: setup sensible hblank value
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Looking at the datasheet, from the TMCI timing graph a hblank value of 2 can
be inferred. However looking at the timing diagram, hblank is not 2, rather
the following equation:

2x t_CONV - t_HSYNC = 52,084µs - 13,33µs = 38,754µs

which results in an hblank value around 1863. Fixing this in the epc driver
lets the tc358746 bridge calculate a correct fifosize.

Signed-off-by: Rouven Czerwinski <r.czerwinski@pengutronix.de>
Signed-off-by: ian.dannapel <ian.dannapel@iris-sensing.com>
---
 drivers/media/i2c/epc660.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/media/i2c/epc660.c b/drivers/media/i2c/epc660.c
index 8505b1e8a73f..f229f9ba1c7d 100755
--- a/drivers/media/i2c/epc660.c
+++ b/drivers/media/i2c/epc660.c
@@ -651,7 +651,7 @@ static int epc660_probe(struct i2c_client *client,
 						V4L2_CID_PIXEL_RATE,
 						pixel_rate_min, pixel_rate_max,
 						1, pixel_rate_max);
-	hblank = 2;
+	hblank = 1860;
 	epc660->hblank = v4l2_ctrl_new_std(
 				&epc660->hdl, &epc660_ctrl_ops, V4L2_CID_HBLANK,
 				hblank, hblank, 1, hblank);
-- 
2.25.1

